               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-222-person1938">
                  THOMAS 
                  KENWARD
               <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1938" type="surname" value="KENWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1938" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1938" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mrs. Fanny Sanson, who lives at <placeName id="t18270913-222-crimeloc1253">Hampstead</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-222-crimeloc1253" type="placeName" value="Hampstead"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-222-crimeloc1253" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-222-off1251 t18270913-222-crimeloc1253"></join>. On the 9th of July, about half-past five o'clock in the afternoon, I saw Hunt in front of my mistress' house; another lad was with him - I asked what he wanted; he said, a drink of water; they went off directly, and did not shut the gate after them; they went down the road; I suspected something wrong - I went into the dining-room, where the cloth was laid, and from the corner of the table missed two spoons; the window was open; they could get in from the front of the house - I pursued immediately, and saw four boys together in a field - I caught Hunt, McCoy, and Maton - I found the spoons on Maton.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Does not Mr. Philip Sanson live in the house? A. Yes; he is Mrs. Sanson's son; it is her house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-222-person1939">
                  JOHN 
                  ADAMS
               <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1939" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1939" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1939" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I received Hunt, Maton and McCoy in charge, with the spoons.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-222-person1940">
                  JOHN 
                  BUSTARD
               <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1940" type="surname" value="BUSTARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1940" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-222-person1940" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended Tomlinson the following day, from the information of one of the prisoners. I told him it was for a robbery at West End; he did not deny it - I took him at his mother's in Somers'-town - I said, "You were with the boys who were taken up at Mr. Sanson's;" he said he was.</p>
               <p>HUNT'S Defence. I took the spoons - I know nothing of the other boys.</p>
